article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 94, Bethune-Cookman 65
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. (AP) -- Bobby Brown scored a school-record 47 points as Cal State Fullerton beat Bethune-Cookman 94-65 Saturday night. Brown shot 17-for-20 from the field and went 11-for-13 from behind the 3-point line as he matched the scoring total of the rest of his teammates combined. The senior point guard broke the 46-year-old school record of 45 points, set by Jon Brettman in 1960. Brown's 11 3-pointers were also a school record. Frank Robinson had 11 points and seven assists for Cal State Fullerton (7-2), and Kenneth Alexander added 10. The Titans have won three of four. Aaron Nelson led Bethune-Cookman with 16 points. The Wildcats (2-6) have lost five in a row. They were coming off their worst defeat of the season, a 52-point loss to Southern California on Thursday night.
